@startuml sequence_diagram_factorial

participant "Caller" as Caller
participant "Calculator" as Calc

== Scenario 1: Valid input n=5 ==

Caller ->> Calc : factorial(5)
activate Calc
note right of Calc : type check passes\n(int, not bool)
note right of Calc : value check passes\n(n >= 0)
note right of Calc : compute 1*2*3*4*5
Calc --> Caller : 120
deactivate Calc

== Scenario 2: Negative integer n=-3 ==

Caller ->> Calc : factorial(-3)
activate Calc
note right of Calc : type check passes\n(int, not bool)
note right of Calc : value check: n < 0
Calc --> Caller : raise ValueError
deactivate Calc

== Scenario 3: Float input n=3.5 ==

Caller ->> Calc : factorial(3.5)
activate Calc
note right of Calc : type check: not int
Calc --> Caller : raise TypeError
deactivate Calc

@enduml
